posts.name: Sam Viesselman
posts.cooked: One of the biggest things I'd like to see is more sample code, code generation, or tuning utilities for many of the COTS products currently available. For instance, we bought several GreyT Telescopes but didn’t have time to tune their PID settings for features like send-to-top or fully retract. It would have been helpful to have a software tool guiding new users through the tuning process. Over the past two years, the community has made remarkable strides with COTS mechanical systems. However, while WPILib has advanced significantly, it remains beyond the capabilities of a small team to implement effective turret or RPM-controlled shooters. Additionally, it’s unclear if similar financial incentives drive software-only products as they do for mechanical systems.
